<p>
    <strong>From the college:</strong>
    <i>If the student has taken Advanced Placement courses in high school and the respective examination with a grade of three or better, he/she may receive college credit. It is the student's responsibility to provide documentation to the Registrar's Office. A maximum of 25 percent of credit toward graduation will be allowed for AP credit.</i>
    <br/>
    For more information, <a href="http://www.randolph.edu/newevents/publications/catalog/Catalog_2012_2013.pdf" target="_blank" title="Opens a new window">view the credit policy on this college's website</a>.
</p>

